/// 4-paragraph sample text about dyslexia used by the Dyslexia Reader.
///
/// Shown on the first launch (auto-load) and re-loaded when the user taps
/// the "Sample" button in the top bar. Matches the React web reference
/// (fork/dyslexia-web/src/src/constants.js -> SAMPLE_TEXT) in tone and
/// intent, but expanded to four paragraphs of dyslexia-focused content.
const String kDyslexiaSampleText = '''
Dyslexia is a learning difference that primarily affects reading, spelling, and decoding written language. It is not a reflection of intelligence — people with dyslexia simply process written information in a slightly different way. With the right tools and a calm reading environment, anyone with dyslexia can read comfortably and confidently.

Reading should feel like breathing — effortless, natural, and without friction. DyslexiaReader gives you full control over how text appears on the screen, so every word is as clear as possible. You can switch between dyslexia-friendly fonts, increase letter and word spacing, and pick a background colour that is easy on your eyes.

To get started, paste any text into the bar at the top, upload a PDF file, or load this sample text using the book icon on the far right. The left panel lets you adjust fonts, spacing, and background colour, while the Accessibility section lets you turn on the Reading Ruler and Syllable Dots to make word boundaries easier to see.

Remember: dyslexia is not a barrier — it is just a different path into reading. Tools like DyslexiaReader exist to make that path smoother, calmer, and a little more enjoyable, one paragraph at a time.''';
